Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 8db5f193b74512d052586bee00ed51bc79ba7a6a

was the redfish validator changes introduced recently? if so could you point to that change here? 

Also could this conversion be done at the redfish side?

No, redfish validator is a tool used to validate if the values set on the dbus property are correct and adhere to the specification. The dbus properties set in the commit accepts a string value, but the redfish validator expects regex validation for the string according to the spec.

It was not caught earlier because the redfish validator does not run on a CI.
could you post the output if possible? it would be easier to understand the change before and after.
